.\" Man page for oci2bin
.\" Generate HTML: groff -man -Thtml doc/oci2bin.1
.\" Generate PDF:  groff -man -Tpdf  doc/oci2bin.1 > oci2bin.pdf
.TH OCI2BIN 1 "2026-03-12" "oci2bin 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
oci2bin \- convert Docker/OCI images into self-contained rootless container executables
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SS Building
.SY oci2bin
.OP \-\-arch ARCH
.OP \-\-cache
.OP \-\-layer IMAGE
.OP \-\-strip
.OP \-\-add\-file HOST:CONTAINER
.OP \-\-add\-dir HOST:CONTAINER
.OP \-\-oci\-dir DIR
.I IMAGE\c
.RI [: TAG ]
.RI [ OUTPUT ]
.YS
.PP
.SY oci2bin
.I SUBCOMMAND
.RI [ ARGS ]
.YS
.
.SS Running the generated binary
.SY ./OUTPUT
.OP \-v HOST:CONTAINER
.OP \-e KEY=VALUE
.OP \-\-net host|none|container:\fIPID\fR
.OP \-\-ipc host|container:\fIPID\fR
.OP \-\-entrypoint PATH
.OP \-\-workdir PATH
.OP \-\-user UID\fR[:\fIGID\fR]
.OP \-\-hostname NAME
.OP \-\-secret HOST_FILE\fR[:\fICONTAINER_PATH\fR]
.OP \-\-env\-file FILE
.OP \-\-tmpfs PATH
.OP \-\-device /dev/HOST\fR[:\fICONTAINER\fR]
.OP \-\-read\-only
.OP \-\-init
.OP \-\-detach
.OP \-\-ssh\-agent
.OP \-\-cap\-drop CAP
.OP \-\-cap\-add CAP
.OP \-\-ulimit TYPE=N
.OP \-\-no\-seccomp
.OP \-\-
.RI [ CMD " [" ARGS ]]
.YS
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B oci2bin
converts any Docker or OCI image into a single, self-contained ELF64 executable.
The output file is also a valid POSIX tar archive accepted by
.BR "docker load" ,
making it a polyglot binary.
.PP
The generated binary requires only
.BR tar (1)
on the target machine \(em no Docker daemon, no runtime, no installation.
It runs the container rootlessly using Linux user namespaces.
.PP
The container process appears as UID\~0 inside the container; on the host it runs
as the invoking user with no elevated privileges.
.
.SH BUILD OPTIONS
These options are passed to the
.B oci2bin
CLI wrapper at build time.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-arch " ARCH"
Build a binary for
.I ARCH
(either
.B x86_64
or
.BR aarch64 ).
When building for a foreign architecture from x86_64, the
.B aarch64\-linux\-gnu\-gcc
cross-compiler is required.
The sysroot defaults to
.IR /usr/aarch64\-redhat\-linux/sys\-root/fc43 ;
override with the
.B AARCH64_SYSROOT
environment variable.
.
.TP
.B \-\-cache
Cache the output in
.IR ~/.cache/oci2bin/<image>_<digest>/output .
Repeated builds of the same image are instant.
The cache key includes the first 12 hex characters of the image's sha256 digest
so tag updates are detected automatically.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-layer " IMAGE"
Overlay additional image layers on top of the base image.
Layers are applied in order; the image config
.RI ( Cmd ", " Entrypoint ", " Env )
from the last
.B \-\-layer
argument overrides the base if non-null.
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.B \-\-strip
Remove documentation, man pages, locale data, and package caches before
packaging.
Affected paths:
.IR usr/share/doc/ ,
.IR usr/share/man/ ,
.IR usr/share/info/ ,
.IR usr/share/locale/ ,
.IR usr/share/i18n/ ,
.IR var/cache/apt/ ,
.IR var/lib/apt/lists/ ,
.IR tmp/ .
.
.TP
.BI \-\-add\-file " HOST:CONTAINER"
Inject a file from
.I HOST
into the image at
.I CONTAINER
path at build time.
The file is embedded as an extra layer on top of the image layers.
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-add\-dir " HOST:CONTAINER"
Inject a directory from
.I HOST
into the image at
.I CONTAINER
path at build time.
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-oci\-dir " DIR"
Build from an OCI image layout directory instead of pulling via Docker.
Compatible with images produced by
.BR skopeo (1),
.BR crane (1),
and
.BR buildah (1).
.
.SH RUNTIME OPTIONS
These options are passed to the generated binary at run time.
.
.SS Volume mounts
.TP
.BI \-v " HOST:CONTAINER"
Bind-mount
.I HOST
path into the container at
.IR CONTAINER .
The container path must be absolute and must not contain
.BR .. .
May be repeated (up to 32).
.
.TP
.BI \-\-secret " HOST_FILE\fR[:\fICONTAINER_PATH\fR]"
Bind-mount a single host file into the container read-only.
If
.I CONTAINER_PATH
is omitted, the file lands at
.IR /run/secrets/<basename> .
Enforced with
.BR MS_RDONLY | MS_NOEXEC | MS_NOSUID | MS_NODEV .
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-tmpfs " PATH"
Mount a fresh in-memory filesystem at
.I PATH
inside the container.
.I PATH
must be absolute and must not contain
.BR .. .
Useful for writable scratch space when
.B \-\-read\-only
is active.
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-device " /dev/HOST\fR[:\fICONTAINER\fR]"
Expose a host device node inside the container.
.I HOST
must start with
.IR /dev/ .
.I CONTAINER
defaults to
.I HOST
if omitted.
.BR mknod (2)
is attempted first; on failure a bind mount is used.
May be repeated.
.
.SS Process and environment
.TP
.BI \-e " KEY=VALUE"
Set an environment variable inside the container.
.I KEY
must not be empty.
.TP
.BI \-e " KEY"
Pass
.I KEY
from the host environment.
If the variable is not set on the host, a warning is printed and it is skipped.
May be repeated (up to 64).
.
.TP
.BI \-\-env\-file " FILE"
Load
.I KEY=VALUE
pairs from
.IR FILE .
Blank lines and lines beginning with
.B #
are ignored.
May be repeated; processed before
.B \-e
flags.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-entrypoint " PATH"
Override the image's OCI entrypoint.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-workdir " PATH"
Set the working directory inside the container.
Overrides the image's
.BR WorkingDir .
Defaults to
.B /
if neither is set.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-user " UID\fR[:\fIGID\fR]"
Run the container process as numeric
.I UID
(and optional
.IR GID ).
Both values must be integers \(<=\~65534.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-hostname " NAME"
Set the hostname inside the UTS namespace.
Defaults to
.BR oci2bin .
.
.TP
.BI \-\-ulimit " TYPE=N"
Set a resource limit via
.BR setrlimit (2).
Both soft and hard limits are set to
.IR N .
Supported types:
.BR nofile ,
.BR nproc ,
.BR cpu ,
.BR as ,
.BR fsize .
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.B \-\-init
Run a zombie-reaping init as PID\~1.
The entrypoint is forked as a child; the parent loop reaps zombies.
.BR SIGTERM ,
.BR SIGINT ,
.BR SIGHUP ,
.BR SIGUSR1 ,
and
.B SIGUSR2
are forwarded to the child.
.
.TP
.BR \-\-detach ", " \-d
Fork the container to the background, print the child PID to stdout, and exit.
Calls
.BR setsid (2)
and redirects stdin from
.IR /dev/null .
.
.TP
.B \-\-ssh\-agent
Forward the host
.B SSH_AUTH_SOCK
Unix socket into the container at
.IR /run/ssh-agent.sock .
Sets
.B SSH_AUTH_SOCK
inside the container.
Skipped silently if
.B SSH_AUTH_SOCK
is unset or points to a non-socket.
.
.TP
.B \-\-
End of option parsing.
Remaining arguments are treated as the command and its arguments.
.
.SS Networking and IPC namespaces
.TP
.B \-\-net host
Share the host network stack (default).
.
.TP
.B \-\-net none
Create an isolated network namespace with only a loopback interface.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-net " container:" PID
Join the network namespace of the process with PID
.IR PID .
The container shares all network interfaces, routing tables, and port bindings
with that process.
.I PID
must be a positive integer.
.
.TP
.B \-\-ipc host
Share the host IPC namespace (default).
.
.TP
.BI \-\-ipc " container:" PID
Join the IPC namespace of the process with PID
.IR PID ,
sharing SysV semaphores, message queues, and
.BR shmget (2)
shared memory segments.
.
.SS Isolation
.TP
.B \-\-read\-only
Mount the rootfs read-only via overlayfs.
Writes go to a temporary upper layer discarded on exit.
Falls back to read-write with a warning if overlayfs is unavailable.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-cap\-drop " CAP"
Drop capability
.I CAP
from the bounding and effective sets.
Pass
.B all
to drop all capabilities.
.I CAP
is case-insensitive; the
.B CAP_
prefix is optional.
May be repeated.
.
.TP
.BI \-\-cap\-add " CAP"
Add capability
.I CAP
as an ambient capability so it survives
.BR exec (2).
Use after
.B \-\-cap\-drop all
to selectively restore capabilities.
.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-seccomp
Disable the default seccomp-BPF syscall filter.
The filter blocks: kexec_load, reboot, syslog, perf_event_open, bpf,
add_key, request_key, keyctl, userfaultfd, pivot_root, ptrace,
process_vm_readv, process_vm_writev, init_module, finit_module.
.B PR_SET_NO_NEW_PRIVS
is always set regardless of this flag.
.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B oci2bin inspect \fIBINARY\fR
Display OCI metadata embedded in
.IR BINARY :
image name, architecture, layer count, entrypoint, command, environment,
working directory, build digest, and build timestamp.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin list \fR[\fB\-\-json\fR]
List all cached binaries with image name, digest, size, and build date.
.B \-\-json
emits machine-readable JSON.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin prune \fR[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
Remove outdated cache entries, keeping only the most recently built binary
for each image name.
.B \-\-dry\-run
shows what would be deleted without deleting.
.
.TP
.B oci2bin diff \fIOLD\fR \fINEW\fR
Compare the filesystem contents of two oci2bin binaries.
Output lines are prefixed with
.BR + " (added), " \- " (removed), or " M " (modified)."
Exits 0 if identical, 1 if there are differences.
.
.SH NAMESPACE SHARING
Two containers can share network or IPC namespaces using the
.B container:
.I PID
form of
.B \-\-net
and
.BR \-\-ipc .
This enables sidecar patterns and inter-container IPC without a shared daemon.
.PP
.B What is shared:
.TS
l l .
\fB\-\-net container:\fIPID\fR	Network interfaces, routing table, port bindings
\fB\-\-ipc container:\fIPID\fR	SysV semaphores, message queues, shmget/shmat memory
.TE
.PP
POSIX shared memory
.RB ( shm_open ,
.IR /dev/shm )
lives in the mount namespace and is not shared automatically.
Use
.B \-v /dev/shm:/dev/shm
to share the host
.IR /dev/shm ,
or
.BI "\-v /proc/" PID "/root/dev/shm:/dev/shm"
to share another container's
.IR /dev/shm .
.PP
Joining another container's namespace requires that both were started by a
process with matching user namespace ownership, or that the joining process
has root privileges.
If
.BR setns (2)
fails, a descriptive error is printed and the container exits.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SSH_AUTH_SOCK
Path to the SSH agent socket forwarded when
.B \-\-ssh\-agent
is given.
.TP
.B AARCH64_SYSROOT
Override the sysroot used by the aarch64 cross-compiler.
Default:
.IR /usr/aarch64\-redhat\-linux/sys\-root/fc43 .
.TP
.B OCI2BIN_HOME
Override the directory where shared resources
.RI ( build_polyglot.py ,
pre-built loader binaries) are found.
Set automatically by
.B make install
to
.IR PREFIX/share/oci2bin .
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.cache/oci2bin/
Per-image build cache used by
.BR \-\-cache .
Each entry is a directory named
.IB image_digest /
containing the output binary.
.TP
.I /proc/self/exe
The loader reads its own OCI data by opening this path at runtime.
.TP
.I PREFIX/share/oci2bin/
Shared resources installed by
.BR "make install" :
.RS
.TP
.I build/loader\-x86_64
Pre-compiled static loader for x86_64.
.TP
.I build/loader\-aarch64
Pre-compiled static loader for aarch64.
.TP
.I scripts/build_polyglot.py
Polyglot builder script.
.TP
.I src/loader.c
Loader source code.
.RE
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit status of the container process is propagated to the caller.
If the container process was killed by a signal, the exit status is 1.
If a fatal setup error occurs before exec, the exit status is 1.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Build examples
.EX
# Build from Docker Hub
oci2bin alpine:latest

# Explicit output name
oci2bin nginx:1.25 my\-nginx

# Cross-compile for aarch64
oci2bin \-\-arch aarch64 alpine:latest

# Build and cache
oci2bin \-\-cache redis:7\-alpine

# Strip documentation to reduce size
oci2bin \-\-strip ubuntu:22.04 my\-ubuntu

# Inject a config file at build time
oci2bin \-\-add\-file ./myapp.conf:/etc/myapp.conf myapp:latest

# Overlay debug tools onto a production image
oci2bin \-\-layer debugtools:latest myapp:latest myapp\-debug

# Build without Docker, from an OCI layout directory
skopeo copy docker://redis:7\-alpine oci:\&./redis\-oci:latest
oci2bin \-\-oci\-dir \&./redis\-oci redis:7\-alpine
.EE
.
.SS Runtime examples
.EX
# Run default entrypoint
\&./alpine_latest

# Override command
\&./alpine_latest /bin/ls /etc

# Terminate option parsing before a flag-like command
\&./alpine_latest \-\- \-v

# Volume mount
\&./alpine_latest \-v /data:/data /bin/ls /data

# Set environment variables
\&./alpine_latest \-e DEBUG=1 \-e HOME=/app /bin/sh

# Load environment from file
\&./my\-app \-\-env\-file /etc/myapp.env

# Read-only rootfs with writable scratch space
\&./my\-app \-\-read\-only \-\-tmpfs /tmp \-\-tmpfs /var/cache

# Run as non-root UID
\&./my\-app \-\-user 1000:1000

# Drop all capabilities, add back net_bind_service
\&./my\-app \-\-cap\-drop all \-\-cap\-add net_bind_service

# Isolated network namespace
\&./my\-app \-\-net none

# Share network namespace with another container (sidecar pattern)
\&./main\-app \-\-net none \-\-detach
\&./sidecar \-\-net container:$!

# Share IPC namespace
\&./service \-\-ipc container:$MAIN_PID

# Run in background, capture PID
PID=$(./redis \-\-detach)
kill "$PID"

# Init process for zombie reaping
\&./my\-app \-\-init
.EE
.
.SH HOW IT WORKS
The output file is a polyglot: simultaneously a valid ELF64 executable and a
valid POSIX tar archive.
.PP
The ELF magic bytes (0x7f\~E\~L\~F) appear at offset\~0; the ustar magic appears
at offset\~257.
The 64-byte ELF header is embedded inside the tar header's 100-byte filename
field so both formats coexist without conflict.
.PP
At runtime the loader:
.IP 1. 4
Opens itself via
.I /proc/self/exe
and reads the embedded OCI tar from the patched offset.
.IP 2. 4
Extracts image layers into a temporary rootfs under
.IR /tmp .
.IP 3. 4
Patches
.I /etc/passwd
and
.I /etc/group
for single-UID namespace compatibility.
.IP 4. 4
Enters a user namespace (host UID mapped to container UID\~0).
.IP 5. 4
Enters mount, PID, and UTS namespaces; optionally joins or creates a network
namespace and joins an IPC namespace.
.IP 6. 4
Applies volume bind mounts, then
.BR chroot (2)s
into the rootfs.
.IP 7. 4
.BR exec (2)s
the entrypoint.
.
